    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Set up ...
        try {
            Object lock = new Object();
            synchronized (lock) {
                while (true) {
                    lock.wait();
                }
            }
        } catch (InterruptedException ex) {
        }
        // Do something after we were interrupted ...
    }

Since the lock object is only visible to this method, nothing can `notify` it, so the `wait()` call won&#39;t return.  However, some other thread could still unblock the `main` thread ... by interrupting it.

