Use the static methods in the [`Math`][1] class for both - there are no operators for this in the language:

    double root = Math.sqrt(value);
    double absolute = Math.abs(value);

(Likewise there&#39;s no operator for raising a value to a particular power - use `Math.pow` for that.)

If you use these a lot, you might want to use *static imports* to make your code more readable:

    import static java.lang.Math.sqrt;
    import static java.lang.Math.abs;

    ...

    double x = sqrt(abs(x) + abs(y));

instead of

    double x = Math.sqrt(Math.abs(x) + Math.abs(y));

  [1]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/Math.html

Try using [Math.abs][1]:

    variableAbs = Math.abs(variable);

For square root use:

    variableSqRt = Math.sqrt(variable);

  [1]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/lang/Math.html#abs%28double%29

